SIMPLE: skillful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skillful
<hw>Skill"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>skilful</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Discerning; reasonable;
judicious; cunning.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Of
<xex>skillful</xex> judgment.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Possessed of, or displaying, skill; knowing and
ready; expert; well-versed; able in management; <as>as, a
<ex>skillful</ex> mechanic</as>; -- often followed by <xex>at</xex>,
<xex>in</xex>, or <xex>of</xex>; <as>as, <ex>skillful</ex> at the organ;
<ex>skillful</ex> in drawing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And they shall call the husbandman to mourning, and such as are
<qex>skillful</qex> of lamentations to wailing.</q> <rj><qau>Amos v.
16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Expert; skilled; dexterous; adept; masterly;
adroit; clever; cunning.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Skill"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Skill"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skilligalee</ent>⟦br⟧
